<DocsLayout title="Customer Portal" section="CRM">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    The Customer Portal gives your customers limited access to Field Promax so they can view
    and interact with work orders relevant to their company. This feature keeps your best
    customers engaged with transparency and control.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>

  <h3>Enable the Module</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Company</strong> → <strong>Application Features Settings</strong> → <strong>External User Settings</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Create Customer Access</h3>
  <img src="/images/crm/crm_01.png" alt="Create External User" />
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Manage Users</strong> → <strong>Create User</strong></li>
    <li>Select <strong>External User</strong> from the Security Level dropdown</li>
    <li>Create the user — they'll receive login credentials via email</li>
  </ol>
  <p><em>Note: External users count towards your total user limit.</em></p>

  <h2>Customer Portal Features</h2>
  <img src="/images/crm/crm_02.png" alt="Customer Portal View" />
  <img src="/images/crm/crm_03.webp" alt="Customer Portal Features" />

  <h3>Limited Access</h3>
  <p>Customers can only view work orders belonging to their company. Key limitations include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cannot see the invoice section of work orders</li>
    <li>Can create work orders (if enabled)</li>
    <li>View is restricted to their company's data only</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Configurable Options</h3>
  <p>Choose what customers can see:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Show Schedules:</strong> Display appointment times</li>
    <li><strong>Show Images:</strong> Display job photos</li>
    <li><strong>Show Documents:</strong> Display attached documents</li>
    <li><strong>Show Closed Work Orders:</strong> Display completed jobs</li>
    <li><strong>Show Work Order Resolution:</strong> Display resolution notes</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>External users have <strong>limited permissions</strong> to keep sensitive information secure</li>
    <li>You receive notifications when customers create work orders for themselves</li>
    <li>Only administrators can configure external user settings</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Offer the Customer Portal</strong> to key accounts who want constant visibility into their work orders.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Review settings carefully</strong> to ensure customers see only what you want them to see.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
